# Language Convention

- English is the project's canonical language: README, docs, code comments,
  commit messages and page metadata are written in English.
- Portuguese (Brasil) and Español are player-facing UI locales. All UI
  strings live in `src/lib/locale/` — one file per language (`pt.ts`, `en.ts`,
  `es.ts`) plus `index.ts` with the store/hook. `pt.ts` defines the key set
  (`Dict`); every other locale file must implement it (compile-checked).
  Never hardcode user-visible text in components. This language set is
  frozen until 1.0.
- On first visit the UI language is auto-detected from the OS/browser
  language (pt → pt-BR, anything else → English); an explicit choice in
  Settings overrides it and is persisted.
- Conversation with the user happens in Portuguese (see user rules), but
  everything committed to the repo is in English.
- UI copy is short and essential: hints/descriptions state only what the user
  needs (e.g. "Volume do click dos botões."), no extra explanations or
  side notes.
